citations:
    citation-affc-arya-i:
        source: source-affc
        properties:
            locator: "Arya I"
            text_from_source: "I only came to find Jaqen H'ghar. / I do not know this name."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "POV: Arya Stark. Arya arrives in Braavos aboard the Braavosi galleas Titan's Daughter, captained by Tradesman-Captain Ternesio Terys. His sons Denyo (youngest, friendly) and Yorko (older, taciturn) are also aboard. Yorko rows Arya ashore and deposits her at the House of Black and White. She enters the temple and finds a man in black-and-white robes who denies knowing Jaqen H'ghar. A young girl (later called the Waif) also appears. The priest tests Arya by revealing a skull face, then transforms into a kindly old man. Arya reveals her true name. Describes Braavos in detail: the Titan of Braavos, the lagoon, the Isle of the Gods (Temple of the Moonsingers, red priest temple of R'hllor, the Warren/Holy Refuge), the Arsenal of Braavos. Arya's kill list at this point: Ser Gregor Clegane, Dunsen, Raff the Sweetling, Ser Ilyn Payne, Ser Meryn Trant, Queen Cersei. Notes the Hound was dying of fever when she left him."
